data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['bʌmpi]
*tính từ
 ■gập ghềnh, mấp mô, xóc (đường)
 ■(hàng không) có nhiều lỗ hổng không khí

Anh - Anh
bumpy
■ adjective (bumpier, bumpiest) (of a surface) uneven.
⁃ (of movement) involving sudden jolts and jerks.
Derivatives
bumpilyadverb
bumpinessnoun

Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
bumpy
▸ adjective
1a bumpy road: UNEVEN, rough, rutted, pitted, potholed, holey; lumpy, rocky.
2a bumpy ride: BOUNCY, rough, uncomfortable, jolting, lurching, jerky, jarring, bone-shaking.
3a bumpy start: INCONSISTENT, variable, irregular, fluctuating, intermittent, erratic, patchy; rocky, unsettled, unstable, turbulent, chaotic, full of ups and downs.
Opposites
smooth.
